  "texts": [
    "Indeed, one might argue that the \"social science\" part of CSS implies or even demands taking a critical perspective.",
    "After all, one can't truly study the social world without attention to the human systems which shape and define that world [53].",
    "Personally, I would like to see critical theory assumed as part of the definition of CSS.",
    "Work that happens to take a computational approach to social systems is not automatically \"Computational Social Science. \"",
    "Rather, true CSS requires a respect for social science theory and an understanding of the social mechanisms which underlie the methods and data we use."
  ],
